limerick_list.text:
This "syndrome": a guy has ignited;
Delirious; hyper-excited;
Lashes out at the cops;
Then goes still, and heart stops.
Cause of death? ExDS is indicted.

I was born on the fourth of July;
I was wed neath a spread August sky.
In September (week two)
I came down with the flu;
In October, they say I will pass away.

I removed your benign dermoid cyst;
Skin and hair mostly — sure won't be missed.
For your fine dermoidectomy,
Please send a check to me;
Don't let your surgeon get pissed.

Zero, cipher, love, nought, duck's egg, nil;
Zilch, zip, nowt, aught and ought, if you will,
All mean nothing to me;
I've a Letters degree —
Doing maths makes me mentally ill.

Perfect sound, upper tier, in the rear;
Like a bell, purest notes to the ear;
No distortion, no static,
Right up to the attic.
What's heard is abidingly clear.

He's a jack-of-all-trades (or tries hard);
He's a queen (whom our straight pub has barred);
He can swagger and sing,
And makes out he's The King;
You have to admit—he's a card.

Biobehavioral tests show one's mood
May be changed by one's choices of food;
Also sports of all kinds
Can affect people's minds;
And some drugs can turn shy guys quite rude.

They amassed on the hill without warning;
We saw them as daylight was dawning.
The enemy faced us;
Our darlings embraced us.
We're fighting a battle this morning.

There was Jimmy, a great tennis star;
Eddie's gang could be found in his bar;
Chuck spat Winchester smoke;
Mike's a ham acting bloke:
They're all Connors — each gave life a jar.

The aubergine: edible fruit;
From the French, its linguistical root
(Latin: S. esculentum);
Gives cuisine more momentum
For life-long "keep fitter"-pursuit.

Time to celebrate, be of good cheer;
Turns the moon and it's Chinese New Year.
See the lanterns, so sweet;
Let's go out on the street—
Dancing dragons and lions appear.

There's a layer of clouds in the sky;
A ceilometer measures how high.
We want pilots to know
When the ceiling is low;
They'll need radar assistance to fly.
